Comment: 0,0:21:55.00,0:21:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,ENDING
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.26,0:01:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Another warrior has perished...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.14,0:01:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was that earthquake... \NDamn it!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.77,0:02:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the evil spirits!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.34,0:02:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to deal with you right now!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.27,0:02:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}T-This wasn't the agreement! Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.61,0:02:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.28,0:02:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Look out!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.91,0:02:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Seto! Move aside!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.79,0:02:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.58,0:02:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Shandoran warriors I know and look up to...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.17,0:02:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...have much more pride than this!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.34,0:02:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.72,0:02:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When this sun lowers in the \Nwest and sinks once again...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.94,0:02:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,...your men's lives will be offered to the gods!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.37,0:03:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.71,0:03:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth certainly swallowed you skillfully!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.46,0:03:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly an act of god! The fact that you're alive is what's hardest to believe!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.27,0:03:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The entire ground?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.95,0:03:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare for the ceremony! \NTake every last sacrifice to the altar!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.12,0:03:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait a little longer!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.96,0:03:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The commodore'll be back! \NJust two more hours! No, one! Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.92,0:03:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we have to be burned at the stake?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.97,0:03:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun is setting. \NThe ceremony should be starting soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.97,0:04:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How unsightly! \NIs this the wreck of a man who defied the gods?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.16,0:04:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you so afraid of?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.15,0:04:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.58,0:04:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You tremble before intangible fears
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.39,0:04:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and give up people's lives for false consolation!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.74,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,False consolation?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.58,0:04:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Your sacrifices are nothing but pointless deaths!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.50,0:04:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have lived this way for centuries now!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.03,0:04:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean it's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.80,0:04:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence, outsider!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.93,0:04:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However great your gods may be,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.47,0:04:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,people's lives are even more precious!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.19,0:04:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the sacrifices to the altar!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.48,0:04:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Burn them at the stake and \Nsend them into the heavens!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.03,0:05:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Commodore!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.20,0:05:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna be set on fire!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.91,0:05:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send an innocent girl to her death...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.75,0:05:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...and have no qualms about it, \Nso I doubt you'd understand!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.55,0:05:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're doing is less than human!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.39,0:05:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No qualms, you say?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.10,0:05:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl yesterday...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.77,0:05:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...was my daughter!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.69,0:05:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You would tell your own \Ndaughter to end her life?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.41,0:05:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you people who don't \Nunderstand how much power there is
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.70,0:05:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in the words our priests hear from the gods!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.75,0:05:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our village is commanded to obey!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.66,0:05:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't beg for our children's lives!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.22,0:06:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one size smaller... \NIt must be the Kashi God's child!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.85,0:06:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods' blood has come \Nto pass judgment on you!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.85,0:06:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Judgment, my ass!{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.94,0:06:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty years ago, my own land \Nlost hundreds of thousands of lives
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.24,0:06:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Kinetsu plague that \Nis ravaging your village now!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.21,0:06:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But, in recent years, there've been \Nabsolutely {\i1}no{\i0} deaths to this disease!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.50,0:06:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.88,0:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we discovered a cure for it!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.05,0:06:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in my right \Nhand is the bark of a Cona tree!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.13,0:06:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Conine I can extract from it is the cure!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.89,0:06:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If I return with this, I can save the village!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.02,0:07:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how many man-hours \Nhave been spent around the world,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.17,0:07:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and how many victims there have been?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.91,0:07:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you people are trampling \Nall over this great advancement!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.16,0:07:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I say your "ceremonies" \Nare insults to those people!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.13,0:07:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Will I die in judgment, or in an accident?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.92,0:07:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Will your village die by curse, or by disease?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.05,0:07:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you that afraid of gods?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.44,0:07:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}do{\i0} know when a man is \Nspeaking earnest words...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.53,0:07:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.53,0:07:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I just kill?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.70,0:07:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A snake.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.70,0:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.33,0:08:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I just broke our commandments and killed a god!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.04,0:08:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you call it a snake, and our \Ndeadly curse a curable disease!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.85,0:08:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you really save my beloved village?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.23,0:08:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can{\i0} you save it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.36,0:08:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.60,0:09:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A-A snake!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.56,0:09:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this...?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.39,0:09:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Calgara! Look at this!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.15,0:09:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What a shock! \NI didn't know that snake had a grandchild...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.03,0:09:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"That snake"?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.82,0:09:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A snake, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.12,0:10:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two make no sense...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.16,0:10:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They were trying to kill each \Nother until just recently...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.25,0:10:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they're such good friends!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.05,0:10:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Calgara is never very friendly \Nwith any of the villagers, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.38,0:10:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen him smile like that before...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.14,0:10:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just follow me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.27,0:10:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We climb down here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.21,0:10:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Climb down?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.86,0:10:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This ringing...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.74,0:10:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Calgara! \NWhere is this beautiful ringing coming from?!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.19,0:10:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow me and you'll see.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.59,0:11:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.17,0:11:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost for words?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.17,0:11:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Shandora, a city of gold. \NWe are its survivors!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.68,0:11:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A city of gold...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.68,0:11:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like I'm dreaming!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.95,0:12:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Whoa! It's gold everywhere! \NIt's a city of treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.91,0:12:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, guys! Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.54,0:12:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.79,0:12:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Load your ship with all the treasure \Nyou can, aside from the gold bell!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.47,0:12:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Seto! Show them where the treasure is!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.97,0:12:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.76,0:12:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure this is okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.38,0:12:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers already agreed to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.06,0:12:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We owe you for saving our tribe \Nfrom that terrible disease.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.64,0:12:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is nothing at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.82,0:12:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so generous, Great Warrior!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.90,0:12:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But haven't your people been \Nprotecting the city all this time?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.64,0:12:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We've protected the city... \Nbut not necessarily its treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.00,0:12:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To be more specific...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.18,0:13:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...only this stone.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.51,0:13:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this? Writing?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.77,0:13:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Writings of history. \NIt's known as a "Poneglyph."
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.59,0:13:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't read it, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.32,0:13:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean your ancestors didn't write this?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.66,0:13:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All we know for certain is \Nthat this city of Shandora
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.00,0:13:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,fought and fell trying to protect this stone.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.88,0:13:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We must continue to protect it \Nwith that amount of resolve.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.32,0:13:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As descendants, it is our \Nduty to protect the proof
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.01,0:13:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that our ancestors fought and survived.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.10,0:13:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We revere our ancestors as if they were gods.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.07,0:13:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I had no idea it was this giant, \Ngold bell I had heard...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.32,0:14:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This bell's ringing has words to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.22,0:14:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Words?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.65,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the spirits of our ancestors \Nwho were greeted by the heavens
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.53,0:14:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,can return to this land at any time without getting lost,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.58,0:14:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we continue to ring this bell, \Nas a way to say, "We are here!"
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.96,0:14:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Its sound proclaims the unquestionable glory Shandora once had,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.26,0:14:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes its existence \Nknown to the ends of the sea!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.70,0:14:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We will never run or hide!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.89,0:14:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we call this city's \Ngrand bell the "fire of Shandora."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.11,0:14:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That explains why it has such a majestic sound!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.82,0:14:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think so?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.20,0:14:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.82,0:14:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This fire reached out to us \Nand helped us arrive here.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.41,0:14:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard this bell in a storm where \Nit {\i1}shouldn't{\i0} have been audible...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.55,0:15:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You like this bell's sound, too?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.18,0:15:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to grow up to be like \Nthat other giant snake someday?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.65,0:15:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably not for a hundred more years!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.07,0:15:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stay here as long as you like, Noland!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.03,0:15:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the first guests here in the 400 years since Shandora fell!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.54,0:15:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to treat you with lavish hospitality!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.21,0:15:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love that! \NI do want to collect plants from the forest,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.79,0:15:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want to see this plague all the way through.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.75,0:15:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Commodore! Commodore!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.09,0:15:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, now. What's with the clothes?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.09,0:15:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, look! An Eternal Pose!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.93,0:15:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And a map, Commodore! A map!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.61,0:15:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We took these from intruders.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.60,0:15:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a map of this island?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.02,0:16:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NThis skull shape is definitely this island.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.38,0:16:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The name "Shandora" means "the skull's right eye,"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.01,0:16:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which refers to this city's location.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.79,0:16:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, take care! \NBe sure she gets lots of rest!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.08,0:16:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Doctor!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.88,0:16:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come look, everyone! \NNoland's giving us some weird crops!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.03,0:16:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a greenhouse on our ship, \Nwith all kinds of plant samples.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.01,0:16:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave some seeds and sprouts \Nthat are suited for your soil.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.61,0:16:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that any good?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.44,0:16:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure is! It's also full of nutrients!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.96,0:17:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Let's work hard again today!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.72,0:17:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Work hard doing what? \NHaving a campfire party?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.60,0:18:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?! \NWhy would the doctor and the others do this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.57,0:18:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief! Noland and the others are coming!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.45,0:18:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen! Do not speak of last night!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.15,0:18:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They said they are going \Nto set sail in a few days.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.58,0:18:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do {\i1}not{\i0} do anything rash!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.88,0:18:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we {\i1}can't{\i0} understand each other after all!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.59,0:18:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how good his medicine is, \Nhe's still a god-killer!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.42,0:18:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they think they're great enough \Nto stomp all over our history?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.43,0:18:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Endure it! Suppress your feelings, \Nand quietly wait for them to leave!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.58,0:18:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.11,0:18:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, guys! Is Calgara around?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.08,0:19:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is everyone acting so coldly \Nall of a sudden? Where's Calgara?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.16,0:19:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are outsiders!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.29,0:19:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Calgara doesn't want to see you anymore!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.89,0:19:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Seto!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.22,0:19:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When are you gonna leave, anyway?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.73,0:19:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.72,0:19:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They suddenly seem to hate us now...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.48,0:19:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on, you guys! \NYou can't just start acting like this!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.69,0:19:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.65,0:19:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's continue our work.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.41,0:19:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have some forest to inspect.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.04,0:19:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are, Calgara! \NNoland was looking for you!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.08,0:19:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I don't want to see his face anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.00,0:19:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If I do, I think I might kill him!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.76,0:20:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The bell didn't ring today...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.52,0:20:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's the first time this's happened \Nin the month we've been here.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.77,0:20:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Commodore...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.24,0:20:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be finished exploring the forest in two days.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.48,0:20:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.57,0:20:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the crew we set sail again in three days,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.37,0:20:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so now's their last chance to \Nenjoy solid ground for a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.70,0:20:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Commodore... \NTo be honest, I wanna get off this awkward island...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.12,0:20:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Only after we've finished our duties! \NGet some sleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:35.05,0:20:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Live here, Noland!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.13,0:20:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! \NWhy don't you make Mousse your wife?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.09,0:20:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.22,0:20:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a family back home, with kids \Nabout her age. I have to go back.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.82,0:20:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Calgara doesn't want to see you anymore!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.56,0:20:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When are you gonna leave, anyway?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.83,0:21:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're here, Calgara! Come out!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.92,0:21:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think this is too one-sided?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.14,0:21:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me why! \NI won't understand unless you tell me!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.55,0:21:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to set sail very soon! \NI don't want to part ways like this!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.73,0:21:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't show your face around me!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.11,0:21:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want your wife to end up a widow?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.08,0:21:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Calgara!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:10.99,0:23:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The bell has lost all its meaning!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:13.71,0:23:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I only did what satisfied me!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:16.46,0:23:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If these were sacrifices for your "advancements,"
Dialogue: 10,0:23:19.00,0:23:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we should never have accepted you!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:22.05,0:23:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They're right to be angry. \NWe have no reason to be forgiven!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.68,0:23:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're returning to the Lvneel Kingdom!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:27.84,0:23:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, on One Piece:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:29.05,0:23:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Eternal Friends! \NThe Vowed Bell Echoes Across the Mighty Seas!!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:32.77,0:23:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!!
